x4freetext: CD2 target with thickness of 150 mu-g/cm2
covered the backward angle of 110deg to 165deg in
the laboratory system. Detectors were 500 mu-m thick,
and were segmented into 16 annular rings on the front
and 16 azimuthal wedges on the back.
four quadrants covered the forward angle range of
detector consisted of a 75mu-m thick dE-detector
detected at backward angles in coincidence with
recoiling B ions in the forward detectors.
Radioactive 12B beam was produced using the
in-flight method via the (d,p) reaction, by bombarding
a deuterium gas cell with a 11B beam. The resulting
75 MeV 12B beam was selected using a dipole magnet.
